title: Who Is Daniel Callahan, Suspect In Louisiana's Erin Brunett Murder and Jalie Abduction? | Times Now
text: Who Is Daniel Callahan, Suspect In Louisiana's Erin Brunett Murder and Jalie Abduction? U.S. Marshals in Mississippi told the Tangipahoa Parish Sheriff's Office that they had taken Daniel Callahan into custody in Jackson, Mississippi, in relation to a killing. On Thursday, the state issued an Amber Alert. Callahan guided officers to his car, where 6-year-old Jalie Brunett was discovered alive, according to the sheriff's office. He then guided the authorities to Erin Brunnett's corpse, who was 4 years old. Suspect Identified In Louisiana's Erin Brunett Murder and Jalie Abduction.
